.TH "vmw_cmdbuf_reserve_cur" 9 "vmw_cmdbuf_reserve_cur" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_cmdbuf_reserve_cur \- Reserve space for commands in the current command buffer.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void *" vmw_cmdbuf_reserve_cur
.BI "(struct vmw_cmdbuf_man *man "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "int ctx_id "  ","
.BI "bool interruptible "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "man" 12
The command buffer manager.
.IP "size" 12
The requested size of the commands.
.IP "ctx_id" 12
The context id if any. Otherwise set to SVGA3D_REG_INVALID.
.IP "interruptible" 12
Whether to sleep interruptible while waiting for space.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns a pointer to command buffer space if successful. Otherwise
returns an error pointer.
